<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_3cf77886-61b5-45dd-ac1b-dd84a98460d4" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>C2D3</sptc><title id="_e9d795cd-6301-4cbe-8a03-9968f07fabf9">Swimming pool drainage</title><archive-num>2019: C2.3</archive-num><subclause id="_0911ac0e-0cd3-494f-aa97-63094fb4d3bb" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_dc8e0e35-32f0-4786-93af-61aa6e6d58da">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Where pumped discharge from a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1487_0.7.0.xml#_4cbd9e00-0622-4dfd-9de4-913c80257732" id="_ca42512d-37e7-4909-a758-5507753f9c33" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">swimming pool</xref> discharges into a sanitary <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/9440_0.8.0.xml#_8310df67-b7b9-4f62-b022-0655a2ae4428" id="_cc176f5d-e780-4040-a05d-e61f3873322d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drainage system</xref> it must be in accordance with AS/NZS 3500.2.</p><subclause id="_aaa18859-853a-4575-8c3f-0b12760d035d" outputclass="state-variation" variation="NT" variation-type="REPLACE"><title id="_7953eee3-15fd-424c-a4e4-2342f171548b">NT REPLACE SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>In Northern Territory, discharging water from swimming pools into sanitary drainage is not allowed.</p></subclause></subclause><callout id="_2709676f-42f5-4a52-b062-4a7a8244a34e"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>Consideration should be given to requirements of the relevant <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_38bf6991-96e5-4900-b9c3-e20038ae81d1" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator</xref>. Where a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1376_4.2.0.xml#_12d6153c-4986-4856-80c0-e21bb57af12f" id="_71f219ba-e8ac-459f-8bba-34fb103c059e" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Network Utility Operator</xref> does not permit <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1487_0.7.0.xml#_4cbd9e00-0622-4dfd-9de4-913c80257732" id="_bb417870-62f3-434f-8c50-df9784fb20f5" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">swimming pool</xref> discharge to the sanitary <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1249_0.8.0.xml#_25307451-c7e1-4167-b4de-e5a1af26694c" id="_0c55dd6d-f0a2-4e35-906a-43770eace967" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drainage</xref> system, a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1396_4.0.0.xml#_e3f95f1d-e1cc-4ab3-961d-c99a213a1de3" id="_72a480bc-18c2-428a-9166-93fef1502cc9" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Performance Solution</xref> will be necessary to demonstrate the suitability of the alternative drainage method.</p></callout></clause>